				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Pretty much has to be the OAM then, which is internal the CPU.  If the CPU is known to be good, then it can only mean it's not loading correctly when it does the DMA.  I don't think there is any game that uses sprites without DMA.  The memory access timing when DMA is used is a little different from the other memory accesses, just seems weird that it would be marginal like that.  With a completely failed IC anywhere I would expect it to not run the games at all.<br /><br />Other than the LS139, those 40H368 buffers for the controller ports are also capable of putting stuff on the data bus.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

